   <body>
      <ol>
         <li id="AccProContDocFolder">
            <p>To access a <uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol> folder at the project or contract level,  perform the following steps:</p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Select the appropriate project, and then click<uicontrol>View</uicontrol>.</p>
                  <p>The<uicontrol>VIEW PROJECT</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>In the navigation pane, expand the appropriate project folder, expand the <uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol>folder,and then click the appropriate folder.</p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Inthe navigation pane, expand the appropriate project folder, and then perform either of the following steps:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul>
                        <li>To access the<uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol> folder at the project level, click<uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol> or expand<uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol>, and then click the appropriate folder.<p>The <uicontrol>DOCUMENTS</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>To access the <uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol> folder at the contract level, perform  the following steps: <ol>
                              <li>Expand the<uicontrol>Contracts</uicontrol> folder.</li>
                              <li>Expand the appropriate contract folder, and then click<uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol> or expand <uicontrol>Documents</uicontrol>, and click the appropriate folder.<p>The <uicontrol>DOCUMENTS</uicontrol> list page is displayed.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
